>Varing temperature Of closed water system

Hi Bud,

The relation is this: In general, things expand as they get warmer. 
Of course, if the volume of a system is held fixed, and it's full to
begin with, expansion can't occur.  Instead, pressure increases -
which is a measure of the water's 'desire' to expand. 

Does this help? 

